Serial CLI (serial console)
SerialCLI is a library that provides a command line interface with serial console. It is bothersome to change Arduino's setting by recompiling and rewriting the program. SerialCLI connects to Arduino at the serial terminal and ends with conf -> = ->save! You can save arbitrary parameters. Other than that, you can also define and extend the original command.
The corresponding data types are as follows.

String
Boolean
Integer
IP Address
MAC Address

1. Instantiation and entry settings
First, let's instantiate the SerialCLI class. Pass the class of the serial interface you want to use as an argument. Usually Arduino such as Uno has only one serial interface, but Arduino with multiple serial interfaces such as Mega can also pass like Serial 2.
#include 

